-- Greek Banks’ Capital Plans Set for April 10, Imerisia Reports
-- B y   P a u l   T u g w e l l
-- 2012-04-02T07:50:40Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-02/greek-banks-capital-plans-set-for-april-10-imerisia-reports.html
Greek banks ’ plans for raising extra
capital to cover losses from the country’s debt swap with
private investors will be announced on April 10,  Imerisia 
reported, without citing anyone.  The banks have already submitted the plans for evaluation
by the  Bank of Greece (TELL) , the government and the so-called troika,
comprising the  International Monetary Fund , the  European Central
Bank  and the European Union, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Paul Tugwell in Athens at 
 ptugwell1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Jerrold Colten at 
 jcolten@bloomberg.net  